dct_title_s: Map of the River Jordan & Dead Sea
dct_description_sm: under the command of W.F. Lynch ; constructed under the superintendence by R. Aulick ; from the joint labours of Lieut. Dale & himself ; drawn by G. Strickland ; lith. by E. Weber & Co.
Coordinates approximate and based on Greenwich meridian.
Bar scale on map given in "Miles".
Shows topography, drainage, travel routes, places of historical interest.
Appears in Lynch's Narrative of the United States' expedition to the river Jordan and the Dead sea, 8th ed., rev., Philadelphia : Blanchard and Lea, 1852.
